title: desktop esni not working  . set to 3 in trr aboutconfg all othere settings are the right ones.
content: Hi , am a firefox supporter. esni not working in beta firefox desktop or firefox desktop. setup all the settings in aboutconfig trr mode 3 allso tried 2 did the clouflare check everyting ok except esni. appreciate your help people. thanks for your time in advance.
creator: pebbleshore192

title: Incorrect MathCAD file download
content: Hello everybody. I am facing a problem. I want to download a MathCAD file that has the extension .xmcd, but Firefox interprets it as .xml, which is why file cannot be opened. Help me solve this problem please.
creator: chubarov.zheka

title: congelamiento de videos en youtube
content: tengo un problema super raro resulta que compre un joystick de xbox original con cable y ahora si lo dejo conectado en la pc se congelan los videos osea estoy viendo y la nada noto un micro corte esto se soluciona desconectando el mando de xbox 360 con cable al principio pense que era problemas de drivers o algun programa caundo problemas pero ya desinstale todo y volvi a instalar y no se soluciono actualmente tengo windows 10 interprise ya actualizado ryzen 7 1700 8 gbde ram ddr4 y una gtx 1660 de 6gb ya revise la ram con el programa de windows y no encontre nada malo reinstale firefox y tampoco se soluciono
creator: pablo_k87

title: Auto Login Problem
content: I am being auto-logged into websites I have specificly not saved passwords for in the FF browser. The pc I am using is not my personal one, so to avoid this I would have to uninstall FF after every use to avoid another potential user from accessing my online accounts at these websites.
creator: justinpbrown

title: Give feedback — paused submissions
content: The page Give feedback landing page says: ‘Please check back soon’. What does ‘soon’ exactly mean?
creator: krixel

title: Firefox (7)
content: When I right-click the Firefox tray icon several items are displayed in a list. One of them is "Firefox (7)". Is it supposed to say that? It doesn't on my laptop, and both are running v 84.0.1.
creator: Crunchie

title: Scrolling Firefox Images
content: No response to my post: "In the good old days, enter a search, select "images" and all menus, toolbars, headers,etc. would scroll to maximize the available screen. Now they do not scroll. Is there a fix?" Does anyone care?
creator: jonlar0316

title: Firefox account locked.
content: When I used a new computer to log into my Firefox account, the account was locked. Waited 24 hours but account is still locked. I could not find website that will assist me in unlocking my Firefox account. Need someone to send me another link to my Yahoo email to unlock.
creator: ronsuwa345

content:

title: Problem faced with firefox
content:
When I was using Firefox. The problem which I faced was every time my antivirus used to give me warning harmful cookies found source firefox, even my tracking protection was set to strict. It means that firefox was not able to filter out the harmful cookies (but I used to surf the web normaly does not visited any unknown/harmful website) Then I uninstalled the firefox browser and reinstalled it again, but another day I again faced a new problem. when ever I used to open the browser the popup window comes saying to select a account to continue and the whole browser freezes

I totally uninstalled the browser, and will install it again when I'll get the solution..

title: How to prevent every link I click to open in a new tab
content:
I just came back to Firefox after about 2 months, as Microsoft crushed my OS with their fall feature update. I could not get many items running, and just had to start from scratch.

That being said, I surely do not recall that every time I clicked a link, it would open in a new tab. I mean, every single time. Who ever thought that was a good idea.

Anyone have a clue as to what's happening here? I usually only want a new tab to open when either I choose it as a right-click option, or when builders have invested it specifically in their code, as they know it will navigate away from their site, etc...

I would be most thankful to get this baby back running like normal. Your help is appreciated!

Btw, fresh windows 10 install. The only extensions I have running are adblock, lastpass, blur, downloadthemall and new tab homepage (which just let's me determine the page address.)
creator: davez18

title: Error while creating an OpenGL shader 0:2(12) : warning:  extension 'GL_ARB_gpu_shader' unsupported in fragment shader
content:
Not much of an issue, but interesting. I have an iMac, 2010 that is running UBUNTU 20.04 as a development platform. Everything works pretty well (sound, WiFi, Monitor), but I get the error message above when running a certain application. The same application works OK when using Chrome, although not sure that Chrome is actually using WebGL

I tried tweaking a few settings in the browser and when I go to http://get.webgl.org I get the little spinning cube that suggests that my browser supports WebGL, but I still get that error message with the App. It might be related to the graphics drivers or my UBUNTU install, or the application software itself. Just kind of curious if there is a fix for that. I use the LINUX box mostly for development and I doubt there are a ton of people using FireFox on UBUNTU for web browsing, but not so sure about that.
creator: sscotti

title: Improve AppleScript Support of Firefox
content:
Hello,

As the feedback is disabled I'd like to chime in with an issue that became urgent the moment I tried to get the URL of the current tab (named windows in Firefox's Dictionary). Turns out that's impossible but even inspecting its GUI structure with Xcode's Accessibility Inspector provided with no valuable objects aside from the main window, the menu bar and the "traffic lights" controls. May I kindly suggest for Firefox developers to extend the set of available commands and objects in Firefox's Dictionary to include basic classes and commands for manipulating link references, page loading etc? Thank you.
creator: ilja.shebalin

title: Firefox's interface font size is so tiny in Kubuntu 20.10
content:
Hi, I just installed Kubuntu 20.10 on an USB flash drive. System's font size is fine. But, the font size of Firefox's interface is so tiny. The font size of webpages are fine and I am able to change it in the Preferences.

When I searched on Google, the other users having same problem recommended to add a 'userChrome.css' file with some code that specify the font size to the Firefox's folder. Then, I came to know that Mozilla has disabled the userChrome.css in recent Firefox versions. I also changed a setting in about:config to make the Firefox accept the userChrome.css. But, the font size is not changing yet.

Please, guide me how to change the font size of Firefox's interface. Thanks in advance :)
creator: jeyaganesh

title: special characters in auto-generated passwords
content: I like the Firefox auto generated passwords feature, but I noticed that the passwords only include alpha-numeric characters. It seems to me they would be more secure if they also include special characters. e.g. ! @ # $ % ^ & * Is there a way to include these in Firefox auto-generated passwords?

title: Top sites not populating (and won't be forced to) after Firefox reinstall
content:
I recently reinstalled Firefox (84.0, 64-bit) and I found that the Top Sites weren't populating. They also couldn't be made to hold a site with the editing tool on each square, and nothing will bookmark.

I found a previous question about this from years ago, which was solved when the questioner verified that the History wasn't being created--it was blank--and the person answering the question said something about removing the "places.sqlite database file", which would then prompt Firefox to create a new file by that name, and track history and populate the Top Sites. An article was mentioned in that solution to help walk through the process, but I didn't see any link or reference to what that article was.

That exact same issue seems to be happening for me--my Top Sites won't load, won't be made to save anything, and I have no History despite the reinstall happening a couple of days ago--and this sounds like the solution may work for me as well but I've no idea where to find it or how to execute the recommended procedure.

Would anyone know where to find that article, or if there's an updated method to tackle the issue?

Related: I have Firefox on my phone and on another computer in the house, and I'd thought they would all sync up to share the same bookmarks, etc., but that hasn't happened. Is this connected to the same issue? Meaning, once the History/Top Sites/bookmark issue is resolved, will doing a Sync actually get my Firefoxes all talking together and sharing the same bookmarks?

Thanks for your time.
creator: reay.jespersen
